reviews.text: An amazing space - wish I'd learned about it earlier! I'm able to book my baby in and have three glorious hours to get admin and work done, or simply drop in and have somewhere for her to play that isn't our living room. It's full of toys, the team are so welcoming, the coffee is delicious and it's such a home away from home at an affordable price. Couldn't recommend it more!

We recently celebrated our daughter's 3rd birthday at KindHaus and would do it all again in a heart beat! Ann-Marie and the team went above and beyond to make it a truly memorable day with zero fuss. A fantastic venue and space, all sorts to entertain the children, ample space for to roam and run around, a dedicated-themed arts and crafts station, disco lights and bubble machine as well as access to all the facilities to cater for children - and adults. Ann-Marie was a huge helping hand on the day and ensured everything was set up for us so we could fully enjoy ourselves. Would highly recommend this venue. Thank you again KindHaus, see you soon! xx

I always take my boy there as it is an amazing space for kids and parents, something this neighbourhood really needed, and the staff are amazing! We also celebrated my 3yo birthday party at Kindhaus  and it was all amazing! Ann Marie is super helpful and incredibly nice so it made it all go smoothly!

The Only reason this is not a 5* review is because I believe there is always room for improvement. KH has made Seven's birthday amazing.  They were on point with their parts which helped to alleviate alot of the concerns I had.  The facilities are well kept and safe for the little ones who thoroughly enjoyed themselves and literally did not want to leave.  We did not have our entertainment, no fault of their own and the kids did not miss it one bit. Thank you KindHaus ðŸ˜Š
I recommend just dropping in for some play time, coffee, tea, a little quiet time while you work-not having to worry about them or simply for a change of environment for you all, Ann-Marie and team will make sure you have a great experience.

This place is amazing - I went there today after not having any childcare due to an inset day. Staff were LOVELY (especially Anne-Marie), lovely toys and atmosphere to keep children busy and a good working environment for parents with the option of a quieter space for parents if needed. Really loved it and will definitely be going back. Also they had a banging playlist.

address: 147 Stoke Newington High St, London N16 0NY, United Kingdom
